  • Bluetooth Call & Smart Notification: Smart watches for men women is equipped with a built-in microphone and HD speaker, which allows you to make and receive calls when connected to your smartphone via Bluetooth. The smartwatch can remind you with a ringtone or vibration, and receive notifications from apps such as Facebook, Whatsapp, Instagram, SMS, etc. You can stay connected at any time, even during fitness or other activities
  • 24/7 Health Monitoring: Fitness watch is equipped with high-precision sensors, 24-hour real-time heart rate, Sp02, and sleep monitoring (deep/light sleep/awake), you can also view these health indicators on the smart watch anytime, anywhere, and view the recent data in the APP so that you can better understand your physical health. In addition, women's smart watch also has a menstrual cycle record designed specifically for women to help them maintain a healthy life
  • 100+ Sports Modes & IP68 Waterproof: The activity fitness tracker has 100+ sports modes to choose from, including running, cycling, hiking, skipping, basketball, yoga, skiing, etc. It can record all-day exercise data and accurately track your exercise time, calories burned, distance, and steps. It meets the IP68 waterproof rating and can be used without worry even when washing hands, washing face, or engaging in sweaty activities, but it is not recommended to use it in hot water or seawater
  • 1.85 inch HD Color Screen & DIY Watch Face: Smart watch is equipped with a 1.85" HD full touch screen, delivering highly sensitive touch and unique visual feast. With the companion GloryFit App, you can download more than 200+ personalized watch faces and set them as your dial. In addition, you can also choose your favorite photos, such as family, personal photos, pets, landscapes, etc. as the wallpaper of your watch
  • Multifunctional Smartwatch & Wide Compatibility: The smart watch includes many useful tools, such as Bluetooth answering/making calls, message reminders, female health cycle, weather forecast, music control/playback, camera control, alarm clock, stopwatch, timer, breathing guide, sedentary reminder, raise to wake, brightness adjustment, find phone and other functions. Joautrial smart watch is compatible with iOS 9.0 and Android 6.0 and above devices
  • Satisfy Every Customer: We are committed to providing you with great purchasing. If you have any questions about our products, such as missing watch accessories, or quality/operation connection/charging issues, please let us know and contact us to resolve. Warm Tips: Please wear your smartwatch correctly, the strap should not be tied too tight or too loose, and leave space for your skin to breathe, which will not only make you feel comfortable but also allow the smart watch sensor to work properly

      Its easy to use, looks great
      Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2024
      1.
      From the stylish design to its amazing features, this smartwatch has exceeded my expectations in so many ways. It has really become an essential part of my routine. The color is really pretty, and it goes with almost everything I wear. Whether Im wearing casual clothes or... See more
      From the stylish design to its amazing features, this smartwatch has exceeded my expectations in so many ways. It has really become an essential part of my routine. The color is really pretty, and it goes with almost everything I wear. Whether Im wearing casual clothes or something a bit more dressy, this watch fits perfectly. The watch face is sleek and modern, and its not too bulky, so its super comfortable on my wrist. Plus, the screen is bright and clear, which makes it easy to read even in sunlight. Ive worn it for long hours, and I barely even notice its there.
      One of my favorite things about this smartwatch is the battery life. It lasts for several days without needing a charge, which is super convenient. And when I do need to charge it, it charges really fast. This feature has made it so much easier to use daily because Im not constantly thinking about charging it.
      The health tracking features are another reason Im so happy with this watch. It helps me keep track of my daily activity, like my step count, and sends me reminders to move if Ive been sitting for too long. This has really helped me stay active. The heart rate monitor is also awesome it gives me real-time data on how my heart is doing, which is great for both workouts and just everyday life. I especially love the sleep monitor, which tracks how well Im sleeping. This smartwatch has over 100 sport modes! I didnt expect it to have so many options, but its great for any kind of exercise Im doing. Whether Im running, biking, doing yoga, or even swimming, theres a mode that tracks everything I need. Its really motivating to see my progress in different activities.

    • Caitlin
      5.0 out of 5 starsAmazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product
      nice features, easy to use, provides great logs with graphs and charts
      Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2025
      1.
      Im very happy with this watch. It is very similar to my previous watch (from a different brand), but the layout is better making it easier to use. This item has a lot of features. Its very useful for a great price. I honestly only use two things on these watches: the... See more
      Im very happy with this watch. It is very similar to my previous watch (from a different brand), but the layout is better making it easier to use. This item has a lot of features. Its very useful for a great price. I honestly only use two things on these watches: the steps and the sleep log. The features that the watch comes with include: Daily exercise, calls, sleep, heart rate, blood pressure, and blood oxygen. It allows you to add in music and weather.

      The only con I have is that I wish the strap was designed better. My previous watch had the exact same strap design (different brand watch however). The strap did fine for at least a year, but it eventually began ripping at the point where the watch attaches to it. I had one other fitbit watch in the past too and that strap didnt last long. I assume it is a common issue with these watches. The loops on this watch tend to stretch out allowing the excess unneeded section of the strap to slip out of them and slip occasionally. Other than that, I have zero cons. Only positives to say. I added a bunch of info below about the different features of the watch in case you are interested. I definitely recommend it. It is a great option in this price range.

      MAIN SCREEN AND LINKS
      You can see a picture of the main screen on my review. It has the time large on the top, with a small date and day of the week below. The main screen gives you a quick look at the following for the day: kcal, miles, steps, and current heart rate (bpm). If you click on the BP picture of a heart, it will link you to the section that takes your heart rate. Swipe right from there to look at blood oxygen and blood pressure. There are three buttons at the bottom of the main screen that link you to the sections for exercise, sleep, and phone calls (includes dial pad, call log, and contacts). Finally, if you tap on the center picture of a running figure (above your step number), it links you to the training section.
      When you swipe left from the main screen, you beginning running through the other sections available like the exercise, sleep, call, etc. sections. If you swipe right from the main screen, it will bring out a box that shows you the temperature (if you have the weather connected) and your most recently used links. This box also displays a larger number for the time, date, and day of the week. I honestly dont find much use for it myself. I havent put the music or weather on my watch yet. I imagine it could bring links up for those too, which would be helpful.

      EXERCISE AND TRAINING SECTIONS
      The exercise section shows a graph with three colors: red for kcal, gold for milage, and blue for steps. It gives you a nice little quick glance at your overall daily exercise progress. When you scroll further down, it gives you mini charts on when your daily steps occurred and a second chart showing your steps for the week.
      The training section is how you time yourself when performing certain types of exercises or sports. The main training page gives you links to a category of sports. The categories are regular sports, outdoor, ball, dancing, martial art, and gymnastics. When you click a category, it links to a specific lift of activities in the category. For example, basketball is listed under ball and boxing is under martial arts. When you select the specific exercise or sport, it gives you a three second countdown and then starts a stopwatch. It displays and logs your heart rate and kcal. I assume it logs steps with activities that involve steps. It probably determines the kcals for activities that dont use steps (like yoga or push-up) through changes in your heart rate. This is just my guess. Not sure.
      While you are exercising, you can tap on the watchs side button at any time and it automatically goes to the sections countdown screen. Then, if you swipe left from that screen, it gives you a link to control the music playing from your phone. I love that idea. If you swipe right, it pauses the session. You can choose to continue or stop the session from there.
      No matter what activity type you select, it does the same thing for all of it. The options of activities you can select from is extremely extensive. It has all of the standard things but if you scroll through it there are things I wouldnt have expected to see like darts, alpinism, and bungee jumping. Somethings are in different categories than the ones I would expect them to be, though.
      When you are scrolling through the specific options for a training activity, it is pretty easy to select one on accident, causing it to start the countdown and stopwatch. No worries, though, because it will not save the activity if it has only been counting for a few seconds. It tells you this when you go to exit out. It is a little annoying, but no big deal.

      HEART RATE, BP, AND BLOOD OXYGEN
      Concerning the features of heart rate, BP, and Blood oxygen: these all seem to work just fine. The heart rate is automatically logged by the watch, as long as the sensor is in contact with your wrist. The blood pressure and blood oxygen will only be taken when you open the screen (and it is in contact with your wrist, of course). If you want a log of your blood pressure and/or blood oxygen throughout the day, you will have to purposely open the watches section for one of those, ensure the watch is in full contact with your wrist and wait for it to take a reading. Both take a little while, with the blood pressure the longest. Im pretty sure that it determines these two readings through your heart rate and some calculations.

      Each of these three sections display the current reading (whether heart rate, BP, or blood oxygen), the daily maximum and minimum reading, a chart of the different readings taken at different times of the day, and a chart with the average reading from the last 7 days.

      STRAP, FACE, CHARGER
      The strap is a standard, flexible rubber one. I like when they have two of the band/loops to help keep the end of the strap in place after you put it on. I mentioned what I didnt like about the strap earlier. Other than the little loops loosening, my watch has held up fine so far. I have used it for about three months so far. It needs charging at least once a week. I havent counted the exact days. It is 100% waterproof. I do dishes with it regularly and shower, etc. Ive rinsed it directly under water a number of times. The screen resists scratching very well too.

      OTHER FUNCTIONS AND APP
      I dont use the calling feature and text/contacts. The one time I tried it to make a phone call, it worked just fine. I plan to add the weather and music feature. The phone I use regularly for calls/etc. is an off brand (TLC). I had trouble getting the app to work on that phone. I have the watch attached to an android phone that I own instead. I plan to try the app again on my TLC because it installed fine and opened, I just struggled to connect the watch. It took me a bit to figure out how to connect the watch on my Android too. I never use the calling option on these watches anyhow.

      The app does provide a lot more information on the different stats the watch takes. The graphs/charts are larger and easier to read. There are a few additional things you can keep track of through the app as well. It connects to the app when needed and updates the apps information as well as the watchs time immediately upon connection. The time will get off if the watch dies.

      The watch doesnt come with instructions in the package. You must go online to access those. I figured it out by myself no problem.

      CONCLUSION
      Wonderful item. I totally suggest it if you are content with a cheaper watch that offers the basic options these smart watches are known for. It is comfortable and works reliably.
